Hospitals in Pietermaritzburg are among the worst affected by the public sector strike. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has more. #dstv403 DURBAN - Hospitals in Pietermaritzburg are among the worst affected by the public sector strike. Workers affiliated with Nehawu are demanding a 10 percent pay hike and have promised to intensify their protest if this is not delivered. READ: Nehawu says public service strike will continue The KwaZulu-Natal health department has not responded to requests for comment. * eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports.